      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(read): add encoding parameter for GBK and non-UTF-8 text files (#92664)",
        "body": "## Summary\rFixes #92664. The built-in `read` session tool always decoded text files as UTF-8, which produced mojibake for files saved in legacy encodings such as GBK on Chinese Windows. This change adds an optional `encoding` parameter to the read tool and uses Node.js built-in `TextDecoder` to decode the file buffer when a non-UTF-8 encoding is supplied.\r\r**Updated per ClawSweeper recommendation**: This PR now uses Node.js 24+ native `TextDecoder` for legacy encodings instead of adding the `iconv-lite` dependency, avoiding dependency graph changes and security review requirements.\r\r## Changes\r- `src/agents/sessions/tools/read.ts`: added `encoding` to the tool schema, wired it through `execute`, and updated `decodeReadBuffer` to use `TextDecoder` for non-UTF-8 encodings.\r- `src/agents/sessions/tools/tool-contracts.ts`: added `encoding` field to `ReadToolInput` type.\r- `src/agents/sessions/tools/read.test.ts`: regression test verifying GBK decoding using raw GBK bytes.\r- `scripts/repro/issue-92664-read-gbk.mts`: standalone reproduction script that exercises the real tool on a temporary GBK-encoded file.\r\r## Why TextDecoder instead of iconv-lite?\rFollowing ClawSweeper's review recommendation:\r- Node.js 24+ natively supports GBK, Latin-1, and other legacy encodings via `TextDecoder`\r- Avoids adding new dependencies and dependency graph changes\r- Uses existing Node.js capabilities instead of external libraries\r- No security review or maintainer approval needed for dependency addition\r\r## Real behavior proof\r- **Behavior addressed**: Reading a GBK-encoded text file now returns the correct Chinese characters instead of UTF-8 mojibake.\r- **Real environment tested**: Linux 4.19.112, Node.js v22.19.0, local OpenClaw checkout.\r- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\r  - `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-92664-read-gbk.mts`\r- **Evidence after fix**: standalone reproduction script terminal output (copied live output)\r  ```text\r  PASS: GBK-encoded file decoded correctly.\r  Decoded: 你好，世界\r  Hello world\r  ```\r- **Observed result after fix**: The standalone reproduction script decoded the GBK bytes back to the original Chinese and English text, confirming the read tool now respects the `encoding` parameter for non-UTF-8 files.\r- **What was not tested**: Reading the same file through the sandbox/host wrapper path (the wrapper only normalizes the encoding argument and delegates to the same tool), and reading GBK files on a real Windows filesystem.\r\r## Verification\r- `pnpm test src/agents/sessions/tools/read.test.ts --run` — 4 passed\r- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/agents/sessions/tools/read.ts src/agents/sessions/tools/read.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.read.ts scripts/repro/issue-92664-read-gbk.mts` — clean\r- `pnpm build` — passed\r\rAI-assisted: changes were authored with Claude Code; the reproduction script and tests were run locally in this environment.\r",
